summary: An Ordinance approving the assessment roll of Local Improvement District No. 1646, for the improvement of Thirty-fourth Avenue, from East Pike Street to East Denny Way; and certain parts of certain other streets and avenues therein named, all in the City of Seattle, by the construction of concrete walks and wooden crosswalks, with all necessary appurtenances, under Ordinance No. 17448 and assessing the amounts thereof against each parcel and lot of land and part thereof shown in said roll, and providing for the collection thereof.
